      <strong>My Takeaway</strong><br><br>
      I struggled going back and forth between data accuracy or expression. Looking back, I should have represented the data I gathered in a more abstract manner (ie. not simply 'copy-paste' the graph). I was afraid that the abstract visualization might not express all the facts in the dataset. I landed somewhere in the middle, using food as the medium through which I presented an accurate chart. Moving forward, I hope to loosen up a bit to expressively convey my message through my artwork.<br><br>
      <img src="<%= image_path("images/project-pizza/pizza.png") %>" class="zoomImages" alt="Translated datapoints into a visualization"><br><br>
      And no, you can't just 'walk it off'.
